title.rendered: Durban vs Pretoria, South Africa T20 League, 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Durban: Kyle Mayers, Wiaan Mulder, Quinton de Kock (c & wk), Heinrich Klaasen, Christiaan Jonker, Dwaine Pretorius, Jason Holder, Keshav Maharaj, Hardus Viljoen, Prenelan Subrayen, Reece Topley

Pretoria: Philip Salt(w), Will Jacks, Rilee Rossouw, Theunis de Bruyn, Shane Dadswell, James Neesham, Eathan Bosch, Wayne Parnell(c), Migael Pretorius, Adil Rashid, Anrich Nortje

Venue: Kingsmead, Durban

Also Read:

India vs New Zealand, 2nd ODI, 2023: Fantasy Tips

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 2 games)

1st innings average score: 203

2nd innings average score: 182

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good batting wicket

Wins

Batting 1st: 100%

Batting 2nd: —

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Quinton de Kock loves playing at Durban. In 11 games, he has accumulated 392 runs at 44. Moreover, his last three scores at the venue read 57, 78, and 65.

With two unbeaten fifties and 36*, Heinrich Klaasen is the only player from Durban to have made a hat-trick of appearances in the Ultimate Team.

James Neesham is the only player from Pretoria to have featured in the Ultimate Team on all 4 occasions this season.

Anrich Nortje is the only bowler from Pretoria to have picked a wicket in every game, owing to which his selection percentage hasn’t dropped below 75.

Rilee Rossouw is experiencing a lean run with the bat and has managed only 35 runs, including two ducks in his last 5 innings.

While the pitch at Kingsmead can be slow initially, runs have come thick and fast after the powerplay. 5 half-centuries have already been registered at the venue.

A Tally of 41 sixes is a testimony to the batting-friendly conditions at Durban.
